          <source>Identify partition strategy for your Cosmos DB data</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Learn the best methods of data distribution in a NoSQL database</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Partition design is fundamental to scaling unstructured data collections</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Check your knowledge</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>What causes a hot partition in a distributed NoSQL database collection?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>A partition key with a large number of values</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Partition key values with a large number of matches are distributed across partitions.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>A partition key that doesn't distribute requests evenly over storage and time</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Access that's concentrated to fewer values of the partition key can cause bottlenecks on a single partition.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>A read-heavy workload</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Requests should be evenly distributed across partitions regardless of workload type, partition key values, and access.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Querying a large volume of data</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Requests should be evenly distributed across partitions regardless of workload type, partition key values, and access.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>What is the best way to maximize the efficiency of an individual database query?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Minimize the number of queries to the database.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Running fewer queries does reduce the demands on your database.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>But that's not practical in most operational scenarios.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Spread your write workload across partitions.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>To use your allocated throughput efficiently, both write and query workloads should be distributed across partitions.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Design a partition key strategy so that your most frequent queries don't cross partitions.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn.monitor-azure-cosmos-db.5-partition-lesson">
          <source>Querying within a partition places far fewer demands on Cosmos DB than querying across partitions.</source>
        </trans-unit></group></body></file></xliff>